[src:algebraic-geometry/divisor-algebraic-geometry] A Cartier divisor is **effective** if its local defining functions *f**i* are regular (not just rational functions).
[src:algebraic-geometry/divisor-algebraic-geometry] In that case, the Cartier divisor can be identified with a closed subscheme of codimension 1 in *X*, the subscheme defined locally by *f**i* = 0.
