[src:algebraic-geometry/divisor-algebraic-geometry] As a result, the projective space of lines in the *k*-vector space of global sections *H*0(*X*, *O*(*D*)) can be identified with the set of effective divisors linearly equivalent to *D*, called the **complete linear system** of *D*.
[src:algebraic-geometry/divisor-algebraic-geometry] A projective linear subspace of this projective space is called a linear system of divisors.
[src:algebraic-geometry/divisor-algebraic-geometry] One reason to study the space of global sections of a line bundle is to understand the possible maps from a given variety to projective space.
[src:algebraic-geometry/divisor-algebraic-geometry] This is essential for the classification of algebraic varieties.
